## Installation

To get started with the Shipping Calculator, follow these steps:

1. **Clone the repository:**

    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/shipping-calculator.git
    cd shipping-calculator
    ```

2. **Install dependencies:**

    For Node.js:
    ```sh
    npm install
    ```

    For Python:
    ```sh
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

3. **Run the application:**

    For Node.js:
    ```sh
    npm start
    ```

    For Python:
    ```sh
    python app.py
    ```

## Usage

To use the Shipping Calculator, follow these steps:

1. **Enter the shipping details:**
    - Distance: Enter the distance between the origin and destination.
    - Weight: Enter the weight of the package.
    - Shipping Method: Select the preferred shipping method (standard, express, overnight).

2. **Calculate the shipping cost:**
    - Click on the "Calculate" button to get the shipping cost and delivery estimate.

3. **View the results:**
    - The application will display the shipping cost and estimated delivery time based on the entered details.

## Contributing

We welcome contributions from the community! To contribute to this project, please follow these guidelines:

1. **Fork the repository:**

    ```sh
    gh repo fork https://github.com/your-username/shipping-calculator.git
    ```

2. **Clone your fork:**

    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/shipping-calculator.git
    cd shipping-calculator
    ```

3. **Create a new branch for your feature or bugfix:**

    ```sh
    git checkout -b feature-or-bugfix-name
    ```

4. **Make your changes and commit them:**

    ```sh
    git add .
    git commit -m "Description of your changes"
    ```

5. **Push to your fork and submit a pull request:**

    ```sh
    git push origin feature-or-bugfix-name
    gh pr create --title "Title of your pull request" --body "Description of your changes"
    ```
